KATSINA – Wife of Katsina State Governor, Hajiya Hadiza Aminu Bello Masari has expressed concern with the behavior of some women identified disposing the nutritional food items provided by International Non-Governmental Organizations for their children. Hajiya Hadiza made this assertion when she received the members of Médecins Sans Frontières – MSF – (Doctors Without Boarders) on an advocacy visit led by Katsina State Operation Coordinating Unit SOCU, National Social Safety-net Program in her office. She promised that, efforts would be made to stop women from selling the products, but rather use them to improve the conditions of their children. The Governor’s wife also assured of her support to the organisation, especially in its effort to grow healthy children in the state. Earlier, the MSF Project Coordinator, Malam Hassan Isa appealed to the Governor’s Wife to visit designated hospitals to see for herself their operations which include curing children suffering from malnutrition and malaria in Katsina, Mashi and Jibia LGAs. He also requested that, children brought from other neighboring LGAs to the hospitals be provided with the nutritional food and cured at their respective LGAs. In his remarks, the SOCU Head of Monitoring and Evaluation, Malam Tukur Ibrahim who spoke on behalf of the State Coordinator, said they led MSF to the Governor’s Wife to enable her redeem her earlier pledge to assist in creating the desired awareness of its activities which includes assisting children of poor and vulnerable households in the state. He restated SOCU commitment to support any organization meant to uplift the living condition of the poor across the 34 LGAs in the state.